tldr: The sleep questionnaire app received a major aesthetic overhaul,
  transitioning from a generic look to a calming, sleep-themed design with a new
  color palette, redesigned layouts, and polished UI components. A console error
  related to null input values was also identified and fixed.
overview: The user initiated a request to enhance the aesthetic appeal of their
  sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too generic. The approach
  involved a comprehensive visual redesign, starting with a new sleep-themed
  color palette and custom utility classes. Key UI components like cards,
  checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and the progress bar were updated for a
  more polished and interactive feel. The main questionnaire form and the intro
  section received significant layout and content overhauls, incorporating
  decorative elements and feature cards. Crucially, all 14 questionnaire
  sections were systematically updated to ensure consistent styling, replacing
  old gray boxes with new themed card-style groupings and refined typography.
  During the process, a console error related to  values being passed to
  input fields was identified and fixed by modifying the  component to
  safely handle such values. The overall outcome is an application with a
  calming, professional, and cohesive aesthetic, specifically tailored for a
  sleep health assessment, along with improved code robustness.
